2x-y-4 = {2u+v \over 3} - 4 = {2 \over 3}u + 12u^{-1} - 4
36 + 9y^2 = 4x^2
y = 2 \tan A
x = \pm 3\sec A
x = 3 \sec A, ~~ A \in [0, \frac{\pi}{2})
(2x - y - 4 )^2 = 4(3 \sec A -  \tan A - 2)^2 
3 \tan A = \sec A
\sin A = \frac{1}{3}
4(3 \sec A -  \tan A - 2)^2 = 4(3\frac{3}{2\sqrt{2}} - \frac{1}{2\sqrt{2}}-2)^2 = \left(4\sqrt{2}-4\right)^2
